---
description: Eliminate `as any`, `@ts-ignore`, and implicit any. Replaces with proper discriminated unions and typed interfaces. One file at a time.
argument-hint: [filepath] e.g. src/store/canvasStore.ts
---

Read CLAUDE.md top-to-bottom before touching any file.
Run: npm run test 2>&1 | tail -3
Record the baseline test count — it must not decrease.

TARGET FILE: $ARGUMENTS

STEP 1 — MAP THE VIOLATIONS
grep -n "as any\|@ts-ignore\|@ts-expect-error" $ARGUMENTS
List every line number and the surrounding context (3 lines above and below each).

STEP 2 — FIX IN PLACE
For each violation:
- `as any` on a store slice → infer the type from usage, create a typed interface if none exists
- `as any` on an event handler → use the correct DOM or React event type
- `as any` on unknown API response → create a Zod schema or interface matching the shape
- `@ts-ignore` suppressing a real error → fix the root cause, not the suppression
- `@ts-ignore` on a legitimate lib type gap → replace with `@ts-expect-error` + a comment explaining why

RULES:
- Never widen a type to fix a violation (replacing `as any` with `as unknown` is not a fix)
- If fixing requires changing an interface used by multiple files, make the interface change in its definition file and fix all callers
- Do not change any runtime behavior — type-only changes only

STEP 3 — VERIFY
Run: tsc --noEmit → must show 0 errors
Run: npm run test → count must equal baseline
If either fails, revert the last change and report what went wrong.

Commit: "fix(types): eliminate any-casts in [filename]"